# pyenv
#   For a library or package, you might want to ignore these files since the code is
#   intended to run in multiple environments; otherwise, check them in:
# .python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if having platform-specific dependencies or dependencies
#   having no cross-platform support, pipenv may install dependencies that don't work, or even
#   fail to install them on other platforms. In such cases, Pipfile.lock should be ignored.
# Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to check in poetry.lock.
# poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Pipenv, it is generally recommended to check in pdm.lock.
# pdm.lock

